com.amlibtech.login.data
Class Subscriber_Organization_Portal

java.lang.Object
  com.amlibtech.database.Database_Record_Base
      com.amlibtech.login.data.Subscriber_Organization_Portal
public class Subscriber_Organization_Portal
extends Database_Record_Base

List of Portals for a Subscriber Organization. Controls landing/menu page, root paths for JavaScripts, css, images, application context. Also allows for custom css themes, preselected constants. Controls login method.

ID for the Subscriber Organization. Length 1-30. (table Key 1)

private DFString portal_Name
Name of the Portal. Length 1-30. (table Key 2)

destination_Url

private DFString destination_Url
File path of Landing page of successful login or of program termination. Usually a menu. A prefix of web_Root + "/Portal_Pages/" is assumed. Length 1-100

menu_Js_Path

private DFString menu_Js_Path
Directory path where JavaScripts are kept. A prefix of web_Root is assumed.

login_Method

private DFString_Enumerated login_Method
Choice of one of the four login methods

web_Root

private DFString web_Root
Context root for the application in the application server. This is a directory path and must start with "/".

image_Root

private DFString image_Root
Directory path where portal images are kept. A prefix of web_Root is assumed. Standard library images are kept in web_root + "/images".

css_Root

private DFString css_Root
Directory path where cascading style sheets are kept. A prefix of web_Root is assumed. Standard library css are kept in web_root + css_Root . Many portal css are also kept there.

use_Std_Css_Theme

private DFBoolean use_Std_Css_Theme
Used to decide if portal with use the file "Std.css" in the css themes directory or not.

custom_Css_Theme_Name

private DFString custom_Css_Theme_Name
File path of the portal's css. A prefix of web_Root + css_Root is assumed.

customer_Or_Vendor_Comp_Id

private DFString_Filled customer_Or_Vendor_Comp_Id
A Company ID# can be affixed to this portal. Useful in a multi company enviroment. Login for customer, vendors and employees can be limited to a company based on portal selected.

preparedStatement_Encode

public java.sql.PreparedStatement preparedStatement_Encode(java.sql.PreparedStatement preparedStatement,
                                                           int order)
                                                    throws Database_Record_Exception
Used by Database_Front to encode fields into a SQL prepared statement. The first section is for fields in Primary key. See get_Key_Where_Clause() . The second section is for the rest of the data fields.

Specified by:
preparedStatement_Encode in class Database_Record_Base
Parameters:
preparedStatement - is the SQL statement with ? for values.
order - indicates which groups of values in which order are in the preparedStatement. order values can be:
  • ORDER_KEYS_FIRST used when index fields are at beginning of the preparedStatement. (addRecord(), INSERT INTO ...).
  • ORDER_KEYS_LAST used when index fields are at end of the preparedStatement. (updateRecord(), UPDATE x SET ... WHERE ...).
  • ORDER_KEYS_ONLY used when index fields are the only values in the preparedStatement. (is_Match(), getResultSet_Row(), Select * FROM x WHERE ..., deleteRecord(), DELETE FROM ...).
  • ORDER_KEYS_NEVER used when index fields are not in the preparedStatement.
Returns:
preparedStatement with values inserted where ? were.
Throws:
Database_Record_Exception - if any of the data_fields.DFBase Classes : get_PreparedStatement_Value() fails.
See Also:
Database_Record_Base.get_Set_Clause()., get_Into_Clause() and get_Values_Clause().
